哈尔滨倡议市民二月二不出门理发：别让一个月的坚守功亏一篑。
Harbin Initiative residents do not go out on February 2 haircut: do not let a month of achievements fall short.
澎湃新闻                      。
The news is roaring.
澎湃新闻。
The news is roaring.
有内涵的时政新媒体。
Connotation of the new political media.
澎湃新闻记者 何利权“二月二龙抬头，剃头理发好兆头。
Peng Pai journalist He Li Quan "February Erlong head head shaving hair good omen."
”受疫情影响宅在家近一个月，不少人盼望随着农历“二月二”（2月24日）的到来能够出门理发。
The affected house has been at home for nearly a month and many people are hoping to get a haircut on February 24, the second day of the lunar calendar.
据澎湃新闻梳理，包括苏州、青岛等多个城市出台了理发店复工“指南”，允许符合条件的理发店营业，但需满足“提前预约”、佩戴口罩、暂停烫染等条件。
According to the roar of news, including Suzhou, Qingdao and other cities to return to work barber shop "Guide," allowing eligible barber shops to meet the "advance appointment," wearing masks, temporary perm conditions, and so on.
同时，有城市呼吁市民“二月二”这天坚持“不出门、不聚集、不聚会”，以免“让自己一个月的坚守功亏一篑”。
At the same time, some cities called on citizens to "February 2" adhere to "do not go out, do not gather, do not get together," lest "let their own month of adherence to falter."
哈市呼吁市民“二月二”别出门“后天就是农历二月二了。
The day after tomorrow is the second day of the second lunar month.
按照民间习俗，人们都会在这一天去理发，剃龙头、转好运、图吉利。
According to folk custom, people will go on this day to have a haircut, shave a faucet, turn good luck, Tu Jili.
”2月22日，哈尔滨市新冠肺炎疫情防控指挥部向市民发出《倡议书》称，大家应秉持“于己负责于人负责”，继续坚持“不出门，不聚集，不聚会”。
In a letter to the public, the Harbin Municipal Headquarters for the Prevention and Control of New Crown Pneumonia urged people to "take charge of their own lives" and to continue to adhere to the principle of "no going out, no gathering, no gathering.
“近几天，我市新增确诊病例和新增疑似病例连续大幅下降，今天很多市民朋友纷纷点赞、留言，都说这是‘近一个月来心情最好的一个早晨’。
"In recent days, the number of newly diagnosed cases and new suspected cases in our city has dropped dramatically. Today, many citizens are praising and leaving messages saying it is' the best morning in a month.
”上述《倡议书》称，疫情蔓延势头虽被初步遏制，却只是“阶段性的成效”，不能麻痹大意，“任何一点疏忽大意，都可能导致我们的努力前功尽弃。
The proposal said the spread of the epidemic, although initially contained, was "a gradual result" and should not be overlooked. "Any negligence could lead to the ruin of our efforts.
”《倡议书》提及，今年的二月二情况特殊，新冠肺炎疫情仍然十分严峻，出一趟门、理一次发，就可能让自己一个月的坚守功亏一篑，让那么多人的努力付之东流。
"The proposal said February 2 was a special case and the new crown pneumonia was still very serious. A trip to the door and a haircut would probably bring about a month of missed achievements and ruin the efforts of so many people.
哈尔滨市新冠肺炎疫情防控指挥部呼吁，过一个宅在家里的春龙节，是为抗击疫情做出的坚守，“就让我们待到战胜疫情再出门”，届时，怀着喜悦去理一个自己心仪的发型。
Harbin New Crown Pneumonia Command called for a home-based Chunlong Festival to fight the epidemic, "let us stay until we overcome the epidemic before going out," when, with joy, to cut a favorite hair style.
部分城市出台理发店“复工指南”农历“二月二”历来是理发高峰，澎湃新闻注意到，一些地方已出台“指南”，允许理发店有条件复工。
Some cities have traditionally had their hair cut at the height of the Lunar New Year's "Guide to Resumption of Work," with news surging that some places have introduced "guidelines" allowing barber shops to return to work conditionally.
据《内蒙古日报》报道，达拉特旗新冠肺炎疫情防控指挥部办公室2月20日发布《关于准予理发店复工的通知》，称即日起，该旗境内理发店达到《理发场所复工指南》要求的，可向相关部门申请复工并备案。
According to Inner Mongolia Daily, on February 20, the command office of the Dharat Flag New Crown Pneumonia Prevention and Control Bureau issued the Notice on the Resumption of Work in Barber Shop, saying that barber shops within the boundaries of the banner that meet the requirements of the "Guide for Restarting Work in Hairdressing Places" may apply to the relevant departments for resumption of work and record.
前述“复工指南”明确，实行顾客预约理发，并查验身份证；顾客之间要有1米以上的距离，且必须佩戴口罩；付款尽量通过微信、支付宝等移动方式进行支付；理发公共用具做到“一客一用一消毒”；建议顾客在家洗头，尽量不在店内二次洗头，等等。
The aforementioned "back-to-work guide" specifies that customers can book haircuts and check their identity cards; that customers must wear face masks at a distance of more than one metre; that payments are made by mobile means such as micromail and cash; that barber public appliances are "sterilized one by one"; and that customers wash their hair at home and try not to wash their hair twice.
2月20日，苏州市卫监所发布《苏州市新冠肺炎疫情期间理发店复工卫生监督指南》（以下简称《指南》），明确了理发店复工卫生标准、流程，并提出疫情期间采取预约管理和信息登记，只提供理发服务、不得染烫，顾客之间间距不少于2米等具体要求。
On February 20, Suzhou City Health Center issued the "Suzhou new crown pneumonia epidemic period of health supervision guidelines for barber shop resumption (hereinafter referred to as" the Guide "), the resumption of barber shop health standards, procedures, and put forward during the epidemic situation to adopt appointment management and information registration, hairdressing services only, no dyeing and ironing, and no less than 2 meters between customers.
21日，山东省青岛市也发文鼓励包括理发在内的“十小行业”尽快恢复营业。
21, Shandong Province Qingdao city also sent a message to encourage "ten small businesses" including hairdressing to resume business as soon as possible.
《半岛都市报》就此报道称，这让不少发型已经宅成“F4”的市民大呼“Tony老师终于要复工了”。
Al Jazeera reported that this has led many people with "F4" hairstyles to shout, "Tony is finally getting back to work."
根据报道，青岛出台《美发美容行业在新型冠状病毒流行期间经营服务防控指南》，其中规定，美容美发行业复工后可暂停烫染、护理等项目，停止提供零食，服务器具“每客一清洁”，严控入店人数，采取预约制服务等加强疫情防控。
According to the report, Qingdao issued "hairdressing industry in the new coronavirus epidemic prevention and control guidelines," the hairdressing industry can suspend after work, such as scald, nursing and other items, stop providing snacks, server with "one per clean," strict control of the number of people entering the store, the adoption of appointment system services and other strengthening disease prevention and control.
《新京报》2月21日报道，北京美发品牌连锁企业已有29家门店开业复工。
Beijing hairdressing brand chain has opened 29 stores to resume work, the Beijing News reported on Feb. 21.
北京市美容美发协会会长陈桂钦表示，随着农历“二月二”的到来，预计2月21日至24日还将有近40家美发门店复工，顾客可通过预约的方式到店理发。
Chen Guilin, head of the Beijing Beauty and Hairdressing Association, said that with the coming of the second day of the lunar month, nearly 40 hairdressing shops were expected to reopen February 21-24, allowing customers to have their hair cut by appointment.
2月22日下午，北京市新型冠状病毒感染的肺炎疫情防控工作举行第二十八场新闻发布会，市疾病预防控制中心副主任庞星火表示，“理发是民生的必须需求，这个时间是可以到正规的理发店理发的”。
"A haircut is a necessity for people's livelihood," said Pong Xinghua, deputy director of the city's Center for Disease Control and Prevention. "It's time to go to a regular barber shop for a haircut," said Pong Xinghua, deputy director of the city's Center for Disease Control.
庞星火说，理发店应保持室内空气流通、环境清洁；公共用品用具应“一客一用(换)一消毒，建立工作人员健康监测制度；工作人员和顾客均应佩戴一次性使用医用口罩，以及店内每个美发座位服务面积不宜小于2.5平方米，座椅间距不宜小于1.5米，等等。
Pang said barber shops should keep indoor air circulation and environment clean, public goods should be "disinfected one by one, staff health monitoring system should be established, staff and customers should wear disposable medical masks, and every hairdressing service area in the shop should not be less than 2.5 square meters, seat spacing should not be less than 1.5 meters, etc.
此外，甘肃嘉峪关、山东文登、莒县等地均出台了类似规定，允许符合条件的理发店有序复工。
In addition, Jiayuguan in Gansu Province, Wendeng in Shandong Province and Juxian have similar regulations that allow qualified barber shops to resume work in an orderly manner.
本期编辑 邢潭推荐阅读。
